                                             5648+* 21/11/05 VTOC access
                                             5649+*---------------------------------------------------------------------*
                                             5650+* VTOC access                                                         *
                                             5651+* +0 request type                                                     *
                                             5652+*    0 connect , open                                                 *
                                             5653+*    1 next , gives back the next entry                               *
                                             5654+* +4 address of the DDNAME allocated to the volume                    *
                                             5655+* +8 address of the dataset mask to retrieve  , +0 length (1 byte)    *
                                             5656+* +c address of are to return the DSCB                                *
                                             5657+* return : 0 DSCB returned , and more exist                           *
                                             5658+*          4 last DSCB returned, no more                              *
                                             5659+*          8 no DSCB found                                            *
                                             5660+*         12 error occured                                            *
                                             5661+*---------------------------------------------------------------------*

                                            55346+* in the fourth byte.  The equates below can be used against the      *

                                            55348+* OC, NC, etc.).                                                      *

 D-Loc    Object Code      Addr1    Addr2    Stmt  Source Statement                          HLASM R6.0  2012/11/30 08.23
0                                           55528+*     Multicast Source Filter Structures from RFC 3678                *
                                            55529+*                                                                     *
                                            55530+*   *** These require the inclusion of BPXYSOCK ***                   *
                                            55531+*----------------------------------------------------------------- @DMA
                                            55532+*                                                                  @DMA
                                            55533+***********************************************************************
                                            55534+* SIOCGRTTABLE - Obtain route information. Returns information for    *
                                            55535+*                IPv4 routes from the TCP/IP stack's main route table.*
                                            55536+*                                                                     *
                                            55537+*                The Route entry structures returned can either be    *
                                            55538+*                Version 1, Version 2, or Version 3 structures.       *
                                            55539+*                  Version 1                                          *
                                            55540+*                    - Field IOCN_IPADDRRTMSGHOMEIF contains an IP    *
                                            55541+*                      address                                        *
                                            55542+*                  Version 2                                          *
                                            55543+*                    - IOCN_RTMSGTYPE structure is the same size      *
                                            55544+*                      as Version 1                                   *
                                            55545+*                    - Field IOCN_IPADDRRTMSGHOMEIF contains an       *
                                            55546+*                      interface index.                               *
                                            55547+*                  Version 3                                          *
                                            55548+*                    - IOCN_RTMSGTYPE structure is larger than the    *
                                            55549+*                      Version 1 or 2 size                            *
                                            55550+*                    - Field IOCN_IPADDRRTMSGHOMEIF contains an       *
                                            55551+*                      interface index                                *
                                            55552+*                    - New MTU field added                            *
                                            55553+*                The RTEV3 macro variable controls whether the        *
                                            55554+*                Version 3 Route entry structure is generated by      *
                                            55555+*                this macro.  By default, the macro generates the     *
                                            55556+*                Version 3 Route entry structure.                     *
                                            55557+*                                                                     *
                                            55558+*                When requesting Version 2 or Version 3 output in a   *
                                            55559+*                CINET environment, invoking applications must either *
                                            55560+*                have stack affinity or use the IOCC#DIRIOCTL to      *
                                            55561+*                invoke this ioctl.  Otherwise, the output from the   *
                                            55562+*                first stack will be in the requested version format  *
                                            55563+*                but, the output from subsequent stacks will be in    *
                                            55564+*                Version 1 format.                                    *
                                            55565+*                                                                     *
                                            55566+* Input     - Input to the ioctl is a buffer length and a buffer      *
                                            55567+*             address.  By default, Version 1 Route entry structures  *
                                            55568+*             are returned.                                           *
                                            55569+*                                                                     *
                                            55570+*             To obtain Version 2 or 3 Route entry output, an         *
                                            55571+*             IOCN_RTMSGHDRTYPE structure must be setup at the        *
                                            55572+*             beginning of the output buffer, before invoking the     *
                                            55573+*             ioctl.  The following fields must be set:               *
                                            55574+*               - IOCN_RTMSGHDRVER set to Version 2 or 3              *
                                            55575+*               - IOCN_RTMSGHDREYEID set to the correct eyecatcher    *
                                            55576+*                 value.                                              *
                                            55577+*                                                                     *
                                            55578+*                                                                     *
                                            55579+* Output    - Return_value = 0                                        *
                                            55580+*                  - IOCN_RTMSGHDRTYPE structure returned with        *
                                            55581+*                    field IOCN_RTMSGHDRNUMENT set to the number      *
                                            55582+*                    of Route entry structures returned.  In the      *
1         IXGBRMLT  - Browse Multi-block Output Mapping Macro                                                   Page   89
   Active Usings: PSA,R0  TCB,R2  IHADCB,R6  SRBWORK,R8  SRBSECT,R9  DATAASMIF(X'FFF'),R11  ASM_SAVE,R13
   CVAFFILT_MAP(X'808'),R13+X'7F8'  BFL_MAP(X'81C'),R13+X'7E4'  FCL_MAP(X'834'),R13+X'7CC'
 D-Loc    Object Code      Addr1    Addr2    Stmt  Source Statement                          HLASM R6.0  2012/11/30 08.23
0                                           55583+*                    output buffer, the header is followed by the     *
                                            55584+*                    Route entry structures.                          *
                                            55585+*                  - The IOCN_RTMSGHDRVER and IOCN_RTMSGHDRSUBVER     *
                                            55586+*                    fields indicate whether Version 1, 2, or 3       *
                                            55587+*                    of the Route entry structures was returned.      *
                                            55588+*                  - IOCN_RTMSGHDRNUMENT - number of either Version   *
                                            55589+*                    1, 2, or 3 Route entry structures returned.      *
                                            55590+*           - Return_value = -1                                       *
                                            55591+*                  - Return_code = EBADMSG                            *
                                            55592+*                    This means that the output buffer is not large   *
                                            55593+*                    enough for one IOCN_RTMSGHDRTYPE structure       *
                                            55594+*                    and one Route entry structure.                   *
                                            55595+*                  - Return_code = ERANGE                             *
                                            55596+*                    This means that the output buffer is not large   *
                                            55597+*                    enough for all the Route entry structures which  *
                                            55598+*                    can be returned. In this case, only the          *
                                            55599+*                    IOCN_RTMSGHDRTYPE structure will be returned.    *
                                            55600+*                    Field IOCN_RTMSGHDRNUMENT in this header will    *
                                            55601+*                    contain the number of Route entry structures     *
                                            55602+*                    which can be returned.  Field IOCN_RTMSGHDRVER   *
                                            55603+*                    will indicate which version of the Route entry   *
                                            55604+*                    structures will be returned.                     *

0                                           56162+*%IFABGN1: ;
                                            56163+* /*                                                                 */
                                            56164+* /* METHOD OF ACCESS                                                */
                                            56165+* /*  PL/S - USER DEFINES MACRO VARIABLE IFARXX WHERE XX=RECORD NUM  */
                                            56166+* /*         DECLARE SMFXXPTR PTR(31) OR RESPECIFY FOR BASE          */
                                            56167+* /*         INCLUDE MACRO FROM LIBRARY                              */
                                            56168+* /*          EXAMPLE %IFAR08 = 'YES',           NOTE. THE COMMA REP-*/
                                            56169+* /*                  DCL SMF08PTR PTR(31),      RESENTS A SEMI-COLON*/
                                            56170+* /*                  %INCLUDE SYSLIB(IFASMFR),  BUT ISN'T TO AVIOD  */
                                            56171+* /*                                             A DIAGNOSTIC.       */
                                            56172+* /*                                                                 */
                                            56173+* /*                                                                 */
                                            56174+* /*         THIS MACRO PROCESSES RECORDS IN THE RANGE 00-06. IT     */
                                            56175+* /*         ACTS AS A ROUTER TO OTHER MACROS TO PROCESS OTHER       */
                                            56176+* /*         RECORDS AS FOLLOWS:                                     */
                                            56177+* /*                                                                 */
                                            56178+* /*             MACRO        RECORDS                                */
                                            56179+* /*            ********      *******                                */
                                            56180+* /*            IFASMFR1      07-19                                  */
                                            56181+* /*            IFASMFR2      20-27                                  */
                                            56182+* /*            IFASMFR3      28-36                                  */
                                            56183+* /*            IFASMFR4      37-46                                  */
                                            56184+* /*            IFASMFR5      47-54                                  */
                                            56185+* /*            IFASMFR6      55-69                                  */
                                            56186+* /*            IFASMFR9      80-84                              @07C*/
                                            56187+* /*            IFASMFRA      85-103                             @07C*/
                                            56188+* /*            IFASMFRB      104-113                                */
                                            56189+* /*            IFASMFRC      114-123                                */
                                            56190+* /*            IFASMFRD      124-127                                */
                                            56191+*%GOTO IFABGN2;   /*
                                            56192+*  THIS IS AN SMF MACRO WHICH CONTROLS THE BUILDING OF SMF RECORDS. THE
                                            56193+*  REQUIRED FORMAT IS
                                            56194+*
                                            56195+*        IFASMFR  &RECTYPE
                                            56196+*
                                            56197+*  NOTE: VALUES FOR &RECTYPE MUST BE ENCLOSED IN PARENS(UNLESS ONLY 1).
                                            56198+*
                                            56200+*  PROPRIETARY STATEMENT:                                             *
                                            56201+*  **PROPRIETARY_STATEMENT*********************************************
                                            56202+*                                                                     *
                                            56203+*                                                                     *

                                            56206+*                                                                     *
                                            56207+*   STATUS= HBB7780                                                   *

                                            56210+*                                                                     *
                                            56211+***************************************************************@G742PJW

                                            57925+* %IGWSMF_1:;
                                            57926+*/* START OF SPECIFICATIONS *******************************************
                                            57927+*   $MAC(IGWSMF) COMP(DF104):                                         *
                                            57928+*01* MACRO NAME: IGWSMF                                               *
                                            57929+*01* DESCRIPTIVE NAME: SMF Record Type 42 Definition                  *
                                            57930+*                                                                     *
                                            57931+*                                                                     *
                                            57932+*PROPRIETARY V3 STATEMENT                                             *
                                            57933+*LICENSED MATERIALS - PROPERTY OF IBM                                 *
                                            57934+*"RESTRICTED MATERIALS OF IBM"                                        *
                                            57935+*5695-DF1                                                             *
                                            57936+*COPYRIGHT 1989, 2008 IBM CORP.                                       *
                                            57937+*END PROPRIETARY V3 STATEMENT                                         *
                                            57938+*                                                                     *
                                            57939+*    FUNCTION: Map the following SMF record type 42 subtypes:         *
                                            57940+*                                                                     *
                                            57941+*                                                                     *
                                            57942+*      Subtype 1 - BMF totals section for analysis of overall BMF     *
                                            57943+*                  performance.  One storage class summary section    *
                                            57944+*                  for each storage class.                            *
                                            57945+*                                                                     *
                                            57946+*      Subtype 2 - One section for each cache control unit (3990-3)   *
                                            57947+*                  having at least one SMS managed device attached.   *
                                            57948+*                  One section for each SMS managed volume attached   *
                                            57949+*                  to a 3990-3 control unit.                          *
                                            57950+*                                                                     *
                                            57951+*      Subtype 3 - For SMS Operational Services event audit records   *
                                            57952+*                  written each time the SMS configuration changes    *
                                            57953+*                  when 1) operator issues VARY SMS, or 2) ISMF       *
                                            57954+*                  'ACTIVATE' or activate via SETSMS, or 3) ENF       *
                                            57955+*                  event occurred after VARY of SMS managed volume.   *
                                            57956+*                                                                     *
                                            57957+*      Subtype 4 - A subtype 4 record will be written for    @OY66824 *
                                            57958+*                  System Data Mover session statistics for a@OY66824 *
                                            57959+*                  Concurrent Copy session or for an Extended@OY66824 *
                                            57960+*                  Sequential Data Set when interfacing with @OY66824 *
                                            57961+*                  the backup program.                       @OY66824 *
                                            57962+*                                                                     *
                                            57963+*      Subtype 5 - Storage Class Response Time Section.          @L1A *
                                            57964+*                  Contains I/O statistics by storage class.     @L1A *
                                            57965+*                                                                     *
                                            57966+*      Subtype 6 - Data Set by Job section.                      @L1A *
                                            57967+*                  Contains I/O statistics by data set.          @L1A *
                                            57968+*                  If recorded at end of SMF interval, one       @L1A *
                                            57969+*                  record contains data for all open data sets   @L1A *
                                            57970+*                  in an address space.                          @L1A *
                                            57971+*                  If recorded during Close, one record contains @L1A *
                                            57972+*                  data for all concatenated data sets.          @L1A *
                                            57973+*                                                                     *

                                            66304+*%IFABGN1: ;
                                            66305+* /*                                                                 */
                                            66306+* /* METHOD OF ACCESS                                                */
                                            66307+* /*  PL/S - USER DEFINES MACRO VARIABLE IFARXX WHERE XX=RECORD NUM  */
                                            66308+* /*         DECLARE SMFXXPTR PTR(31) OR RESPECIFY FOR BASE          */
                                            66309+* /*         INCLUDE MACRO FROM LIBRARY                              */
                                            66310+* /*          EXAMPLE %IFAR08 = 'YES',           NOTE. THE COMMA REP-*/
                                            66311+* /*                  DCL SMF08PTR PTR(31),      RESENTS A SEMI-COLON*/
                                            66312+* /*                  %INCLUDE SYSLIB(IFASMFR),  BUT ISN'T TO AVIOD  */
                                            66313+* /*                                             A DIAGNOSTIC.       */
                                            66314+* /*                                                                 */
                                            66315+* /*                                                                 */
                                            66316+* /*         THIS MACRO PROCESSES RECORDS IN THE RANGE 00-06. IT     */
                                            66317+* /*         ACTS AS A ROUTER TO OTHER MACROS TO PROCESS OTHER       */
                                            66318+* /*         RECORDS AS FOLLOWS:                                     */
                                            66319+* /*                                                                 */
                                            66320+* /*             MACRO        RECORDS                                */
                                            66321+* /*            ********      *******                                */
                                            66322+* /*            IFASMFR1      07-19                                  */
                                            66323+* /*            IFASMFR2      20-27                                  */
                                            66324+* /*            IFASMFR3      28-36                                  */
                                            66325+* /*            IFASMFR4      37-46                                  */
                                            66326+* /*            IFASMFR5      47-54                                  */
                                            66327+* /*            IFASMFR6      55-69                                  */
                                            66328+* /*            IFASMFR9      80-84                              @07C*/
                                            66329+* /*            IFASMFRA      85-103                             @07C*/

                                            66701+*01* EXTERNAL CLASSIFICATION:  GUPI
                                            66702+*01* END OF EXTERNAL CLASSIFICATION:
                                            66703+*
                                            66704+*01* FUNCTION:
                                            66705+*
                                            66706+*      The SMFRCD92 maps the structure of SMF record type 92 which
                                            66707+*      is written at OpenMVS file open or close, file system
                                            66708+*      mount, remount or unmount, file system suspend or resume,
                                            66709+*      and file memory map or unmap.
                                            66710+*
                                            66711+*      This is a CBGEN part, see the notes below before changing.
                                            66712+*
                                            66713+*01* METHOD OF ACCESS:
                                            66714+*
                                            66715+*02*   PL/X:
                                            66716+*
                                            66717+*        %INCLUDE SYSLIB(BPXYSMFR)
                                            66718+*        By default, the SMFRCD92 is based on SMF92PTR. If
                                            66719+*        other basing is desired, use %SMFRBASE='BASED(XXXXXX)'.
                                            66720+*        If %SMFRBASE='BASED(SMF92PTR)' is coded, a declare for
                                            66721+*        SMF92PTR is also generated.
                                            66722+*
                                            66723+*01* SIZE:
                                            66724+*            SMF92ESA -- X'0490' bytes

                                            66728+*            SMF92ID  -- X'0048' bytes
                                            66729+*            SMF92FSM -- X'006C' bytes
                                            66730+*            SMF92FSP -- X'0002' bytes

                                            67328+*/*                                                                  *
                                            67329+*                                                                    *
                                            67330+*   Macro Name: ERBSMF79                                             *
                                            67331+*                                                                    *
                                            67332+*   Descriptive Name: Mapping Macro for SMF record type 79           *
                                            67333+*                     (Monitor II) with following subtypes:          *
                                            67334+*                                                                    *
                                            67335+*                       1 - Address Space State Data                 *
                                            67336+*                       2 - Address Space Resource Data              *
                                            67337+*                       3 - Storage/Processor (SRCS) Data            *
                                            67338+*                       4 - Paging Activity                          *
                                            67339+*                       5 - Address Space SRM Data                   *
                                            67340+*                       6 - Reserve (SENQR) Data                     *
                                            67341+*                       7 - Enqueue Contention (SENQ) Data           *
                                            67342+*                       9 - Device Activity                          *
                                            67343+*                      11 - Page Data Set Activity                   *
                                            67344+*                      12 - Channel Path Activity                    *
                                            67345+*                      14 - I/O Queuing Activity                     *
                                            67346+*                      15 - IRLM Long Lock Detection                 *
                                            67347+*                                                                    *
                                            67348+*                                                                    *
                                            67349+*   DSECT names: SMF79HDR, SMF79PRO, R79CHL,                         *
                                            67350+*                R791ELEM,                                           *
                                            67351+*                R792ELEM,                                           *
                                            67352+*                R793,                                               *
                                            67353+*                R794,                                               *
                                            67354+*                R795ELEM,                                           *
                                            67355+*                R796ELEM,                                           *
                                            67356+*                R797ELEM,                                           *
                                            67357+*                R798ELEM,                                           *
                                            67358+*                R799ELEM,                                           *
                                            67359+*                R79AELEM,                                           *
                                            67360+*                R79BCNTL, R79BELEM,                                 *
                                            67361+*                R79CCNTL, R79CCHNL                                  *
                                            67362+*                R79DCS, R79DCPD, R79DDS,                            *
                                            67363+*                R79EGD, R79ECS, R79ECPD, R79EDS                     *
                                            67364+*                R79FIRLM                                        @F1A*
                                            67365+*                                                                    *
                                            67366+*                                                                    *
                                            67367+*   Function: This macro maps the complete SMF record type 79        *
                                            67368+*             The record consists of 5 parts:                        *
                                            67369+*             1. The fixed portion of the SMF header.                *
                                            67370+*                This mapping is invoked by calling macro ERBHDR.    *
1         BPXYSMFR  - OpenMVS File System SMF Record format                                                     Page  309
   Active Usings: PSA,R0  TCB,R2  IHADCB,R6  SRBWORK,R8  SRBSECT,R9  DATAASMIF(X'FFF'),R11  ASM_SAVE,R13

 D-Loc    Object Code      Addr1    Addr2    Stmt  Source Statement                          HLASM R6.0  2012/11/30 08.23
0                                           67371+*             2. The individual header extension which               *
                                            67372+*                contains offset/length/number triplets              *
                                            67373+*                to address the record parts following the           *
                                            67374+*                RMF product section.                                *
                                            67375+*             3. The RMF product section.                            *
                                            67376+*                This mapping is invoked by calling macro ERBPRO.    *
                                            67377+*             4. The RMF data control section.                       *
                                            67378+*             5. The RMF data sections.                              *
                                            67379+*                                                                    *

                                            69229+*01* Macro Name: ERBSMF70                                            *
                                            69230+*                                                                    *
                                            69231+*01* Descriptive Name:  SMF record 70 subtype 1 and 2                *
                                            69232+*02* Acronym: SMF70                                                  *
                                            69233+*                                                                    *
                                            69234+*01* DSECT Name:                                                     *
                                            69235+*02* Subtype 1: SMF70HDR SMF70PRO SMF70CTL SMF70CPU                  *
                                            69236+*02*            SMF70AID SMF70BCT SMF70BPD SMF70CIS                  *
                                            69237+*02* Subtype 2: SMF70HDR SMF70PRO R702TYP3 R702TYP4                  *
                                            69238+*               R702CCF                                              *
                                            69239+*                                                                    *
                                            69240+*01* Component: Resource Measurement Facility (27404)                *
                                            69241+*                                                                    *
                                            69242+*01* Eye-Catcher: None                                               *
                                            69243+*02*  Offset: N/A                                                    *
                                            69244+*02*  Length: N/A                                                    *
                                            69245+*                                                                    *
                                            69246+*01* Storage Attributes:                                             *
                                            69247+*02*   Subpool: 1                                                    *
                                            69248+*02*   Key: 0                                                        *
                                            69249+*02*   Residency: Any                                                *
                                            69250+*02*   Main Storage: N/A                                             *
                                            69251+*02*   Auxiliary Storage: N/A                                        *
                                            69252+*02*   Virtual Storage: N/A                                          *
                                            69253+*                                                                    *
                                            69254+*01* Function = This macro maps the complete SMF record type 70.     *
                                            69255+*                                                                    *
                                            69256+*              It has two subtypes:                                  *
                                            69257+*                                                                    *
                                            69258+*              - Subtype 1 is created by RMF if CPU activity         *
                                            69259+*                measurements are activated.                         *
                                            69260+*              - Subtype 2 is created by RMF if Crypto activity      *
                                            69261+*                measurements are activated.                         *
                                            69262+*                                                                    *
                                            69263+*              The record consists of 4 parts:                       *
                                            69264+*                                                                    *
                                            69265+*              1. The fixed portion of the SMF header.               *
                                            69266+*                 This mapping is invoked by calling ERBHDR macro.   *
                                            69267+*              2. The individual header extension which contains     *
                                            69268+*                 offset/length/number triplets to address the       *
                                            69269+*                 record parts following the RMF product section.    *
                                            69270+*              3. The RMF product section.                           *
                                            69271+*                 This mapping is invoked by calling ERBPRO macro.   *
                                            69272+*              4. The RMF data sections                              *
                                            69273+*                                                                    *
                                            69274+*01* Notes: None                                                     *
                                            69275+*                                                                    *
1         BPXYSMFR  - OpenMVS File System SMF Record format                                                     Page  344

0                                           70575+*    Optionally, the parameter area can point to a symbol table
                                            70576+*    (SYMBT) which consists of the SYMBT header plus SYMBTE entries
                                            70577+*    (which immediately follow the header, or are pointed to by
                                            70578+*    a field which immediately follows the header).
                                            70579+*
                                            70580+*02* Return information is provided in the fullword pointed to by
                                            70581+*    field SymbpReturnCode@. Possible values are:
                                            70582+*03* 0
                                            70583+*03*    Meaning: Successful Completion. All requested substitution
                                            70584+*                was performed.
                                            70585+*03*    Action:  None required.
                                            70586+*
                                            70587+*03* 4
                                            70588+*03*    Meaning: Warning. When Substring was specified, a substring
                                            70589+*                that exceeded the bounds of the substitution text,
                                            70590+*                or a substring in which the length was specified
                                            70591+*                as 0, was found.
                                            70592+*                Substitution continues.
                                            70593+*03*    Action:  None required.
                                            70594+*
                                            70595+*03* 8
                                            70596+*03*    Meaning: Warning. Target buffer was too small to contain
                                            70597+*                all of the substitution text.
                                            70598+*03*    Action:  Specify a larger target buffer, or continue
                                            70599+*                processing using the value returned in the fullword
                                            70600+*                pointed to by field SymbpTargetLength@ to determine
                                            70601+*                how much data was placed into the target buffer.
                                            70602+*
                                            70603+*03* 12
                                            70604+*03*    Meaning: Error. When CheckNull was specified, a substitution
                                            70605+*                text length of 0 was encountered when performing
                                            70606+*                substitution. Substitution continues.
                                            70607+*03*    Action:  None required. The system informs the program of the
                                            70608+*                situation in which it was interested. It is up to
                                            70609+*                the program to determine the necessary course of
                                            70610+*                action.
                                            70611+*
                                            70612+*03* 16
                                            70613+*03*    Meaning: Warning. When WarnNoSub was specified, the
                                            70614+*                substitution process encountered no symbols for
                                            70615+*                which to substitute.
                                            70616+*                The substitution processing completed normally.
                                            70617+*03*    Action:  None required.
                                            70618+*
                                            70619+*01* METHOD OF ACCESS:
                                            70620+*02*  ASM:
                                            70621+*      ASASYMBP
                                            70622+*           DSECT=YES|NO  -- Request DSECT definition
                                            70623+*           SYMBP=YES|NO|COND -- Request parameter area mapping
                                            70624+*                            USING on SYMBP
                                            70625+*           SYMBT=YES|NO|COND -- Request symbol table mapping
                                            70626+*                            USING on SYMBT
                                            70627+*           SYMBTE=YES|NO|COND -- Request symbol table entry mapping
                                            70628+*                            USING on SYMBTE
                                            70629+*     Default: DSECT=YES,SYMBP=YES,SYMBT=COND,SYMBTE=COND
